width: an integer representing the width of a box.
height: an integer representing the height of a box.
mass: an integer representing the mass of a box.
The function first sets two boolean variables isBulky and isHeavy to false.

Then, it checks if the mass of the box is greater than or equal to 100 and sets the isHeavy variable to true if it is.

Next, it calculates the volume of the box by multiplying its length, width, and height, and saves the result in a variable vol. If the length, width, or height of the box is greater than or equal to 10000 or if the volume of the box is greater than or equal to 1000000000, the isBulky variable is set to true.

Finally, the function returns a string value based on the values of isBulky and isHeavy:

"Both" if both isHeavy and isBulky are true.
"Heavy" if only isHeavy is true.
"Bulky" if only isBulky is true.
"Neither" if both isHeavy and isBulky are false.
