The time complexity of this solution is O(1). This is because the code performs a fixed number of comparisons and calculations regardless of the input values. The conditions for checking "Heavy" and "Bulky" are straightforward and don't involve iterations or recursion.

- Space complexity:
The space complexity of this solution is O(1) as well. The code uses a constant amount of memory to store the boolean variables bulky and heavy, as well as the volume variable. These variables don't scale with the input, so the space complexity remains constant.

